FREE STATE police have launched a manhunt after an ATM was bombed at Sunrise Supermarket, Bush Tshabalala Avenue on Friday, 24 February. According to Captain Stephen Thakeng, at about 3:10am, the ATM was blown open by explosives and the machine was extensively damaged. “When members of Thabong responded to the crime scene, two shots were fired in their direction, but nobody was shot or sustained any injuries. Four men fled the scene,” Thakeng said in a statement. He said members of the Explosive Section were summoned to the scene. They found remnants of shock tube starter, brown box tape with a small quantity of explosives, swabs, control samples and money with dye stains. Anyone with information about these suspects should contact Thabong Police Station at 082 301 2809 or Crime Stop at 08600 10111.